00:46:45.220 --> 00:46:51.970
and the amputees needed
medication and also laughter.

00:46:51.970 --> 00:46:57.300
And at the same time a man
left, he was 26 years old,

00:46:57.300 --> 00:47:03.420
left Brooklyn as a lieutenant, and
he was sent to occupied France.

00:47:03.420 --> 00:47:09.590
And he was very scared of being
in the combat zone, terrified.

00:47:09.590 --> 00:47:17.720
And he was awarded the [inaudible]
by the French for his bravery.

00:47:17.720 --> 00:47:23.050
I got letters from both of them
from the Library of Congress.

00:47:23.050 --> 00:47:29.230
By sheer chance I looked through
2,000 names before I found theirs.

00:47:29.230 --> 00:47:32.860
And then I asked what,
if anything, they had.

00:47:32.860 --> 00:47:36.280
It was one box, and there
were 69 letters there.

00:47:36.280 --> 00:47:41.330
And then the family in Princeton
and Wisconsin opened up to me,

00:47:41.330 --> 00:47:43.780
and the deluged me with documents.

00:47:43.780 --> 00:47:48.870
I hope it will come
out before the Library

00:47:48.870 --> 00:47:55.740
of Congress has their exhibition
on World War I planned for 2017.

00:47:55.740 --> 00:48:00.540
But their experiences are
not only about this war,

00:48:00.540 --> 00:48:04.350
the terrible facial wounds
and things like that,

00:48:04.350 --> 00:48:07.130
his experiences in warfare.

00:48:07.130 --> 00:48:11.750
Twice in one day he
was almost killed.

00:48:11.750 --> 00:48:15.840
Once he was in a trench,
and a German soldier jumped

00:48:15.840 --> 00:48:17.850
over with a bayonet
and tried to stab him.

00:48:17.850 --> 00:48:22.310 position:56%
They literally had hand-to-hand
combat before he plunged the bayonet

00:48:22.310 --> 00:48:24.030
in his enemy.

00:48:24.030 --> 00:48:27.900
And then he was in the same
trench when the walls caved in

00:48:27.900 --> 00:48:31.190
and he was buried alive almost.

00:48:31.190 --> 00:48:34.630
This telegram runner saw this,

00:48:34.630 --> 00:48:37.070
went back to headquarters
and said he's dead.

00:48:37.070 --> 00:48:40.540
They sent a telegram to
his father in Brooklyn

00:48:40.540 --> 00:48:44.660
from a state assemblyman, and
they said your son is dead.

00:48:44.660 --> 00:48:48.260
And he walked around for two
hours wondering how he was going

00:48:48.260 --> 00:48:49.680
to tell his wife.

00:48:49.680 --> 00:48:51.730 position:56%
And then he went back to the office,

00:48:51.730 --> 00:48:54.510
and another cable came
and said he's alive.

00:48:54.510 --> 00:48:56.520
He hadn't told his mother.

00:48:56.520 --> 00:48:59.060
So his experiences
and her experiences.

00:48:59.060 --> 00:49:00.740
Now, that's not the
end of the story.

00:49:00.740 --> 00:49:06.190
They came back on the same
ship and they met each other.

00:49:06.190 --> 00:49:08.880
There were 4,000 people there,

00:49:08.880 --> 00:49:12.040
and they met each other
and they married.

00:49:12.040 --> 00:49:17.340
And her fianc was waiting on
shore but he lost out, he lost out.

00:49:17.340 --> 00:49:22.300
And they married and they had one
who became a world famous physicist

00:49:22.300 --> 00:49:26.030
at Princeton, world
famous, died of leukemia.

00:49:26.030 --> 00:49:30.320
And his daughter and his
second wife are the people

00:49:30.320 --> 00:49:33.700
who deluged me with information.

00:49:34.740 --> 00:49:36.160
&gt;&gt; Michlean Amir: Well, that sounds

00:49:36.160 --> 00:49:40.820
like a more upbeat
story of an awful war.

00:49:40.820 --> 00:49:43.430
I think that World
War I was overshadowed

00:49:43.430 --> 00:49:47.270
by the horrible atrocities
of World War II.

00:49:47.270 --> 00:49:50.920
And there's a lot that needs to
be told still about World War I.

00:49:50.920 --> 00:49:54.230
So it's excellent that
you're doing that.

00:49:54.230 --> 00:49:55.530
Nancy?

00:49:55.530 --> 00:49:56.830
&gt;&gt; Nancy Geise: Thank you.

00:49:56.830 --> 00:49:58.940
I have another book, but it's
long term off before I even really

00:49:58.940 --> 00:50:00.240
start writing.

00:50:00.240 --> 00:50:03.160
Because when I write I can't
do much of anything else.

00:50:03.160 --> 00:50:07.230
And I really feel like I owe it
to Joe to do everything I can

00:50:07.230 --> 00:50:08.620
to get the word about this book

00:50:08.620 --> 00:50:11.510
out because I feel like
it is so important.

00:50:11.510 --> 00:50:15.530
And so I'm dedicating my time
to speaking about Joe's story.

00:50:15.530 --> 00:50:18.910
So if you have any other contacts
let me know around the world.

00:50:18.910 --> 00:50:20.580
I would love to speak there.

00:50:20.580 --> 00:50:27.060
And I'd love to see it as a
movie someday and a documentary.

00:50:27.060 --> 00:50:28.360
So there's a lot of things.

00:50:28.360 --> 00:50:30.870
We are in production right
now for an audio book.

00:50:30.870 --> 00:50:32.170
And this was so cool.

00:50:32.170 --> 00:50:34.410
About three weeks ago I
was in Colorado with Joe.

00:50:34.410 --> 00:50:36.980
We took him into this
recording studio.

00:50:36.980 --> 00:50:40.430
We were able to record Joe
reading his opening quotes

00:50:40.430 --> 00:50:42.490
at the beginning of every chapter.

00:50:42.490 --> 00:50:45.720
So I think that will be
really powerful as well.

00:50:45.720 --> 00:50:49.120
Because without a driving force
behind somebody behind a book they

00:50:49.120 --> 00:50:52.650
don't do much.

00:50:52.650 --> 00:50:56.980
&gt;&gt; I was wondering if any of
you have had a personal face-

00:50:56.980 --> 00:50:59.170
to-face confrontation with someone

00:50:59.170 --> 00:51:03.890
who is a known Holocaust
denier and what happened.

00:51:03.890 --> 00:51:07.420
Or if it hadn't happened what
do you think might happen?

00:51:07.420 --> 00:51:11.080
&gt;&gt; Michlean Amir: The
question is about any interface

00:51:11.080 --> 00:51:13.330
with the Holocaust denier.

00:51:13.330 --> 00:51:18.940 position:56%
I know Nancy has a story about that,
and perhaps Tony has in addition

00:51:18.940 --> 00:51:23.030
to what he already said
about the French neo-Nazi.

00:51:23.030 --> 00:51:24.330
Nancy?

00:51:24.330 --> 00:51:27.310
&gt;&gt; Well, it was interesting.

00:51:27.310 --> 00:51:31.040
After we recorded Joe's
voice for the audio book,

00:51:31.040 --> 00:51:34.050
I posted it on Facebook what
a neat experience that was.

00:51:34.050 --> 00:51:38.100
And some woman, not a Holocaust
denier, but someone posted

00:51:38.100 --> 00:51:42.580 position:56%
on my Facebook, my profession
Facebook page, that, oh, that woman,

00:51:42.580 --> 00:51:44.660
meaning me, was just
making this all up.

00:51:44.660 --> 00:51:46.650
That Joe is really dead.

00:51:46.650 --> 00:51:48.510
That he's been dead a long time.

00:51:48.510 --> 00:51:49.810
That there's no such thing

00:51:49.810 --> 00:51:53.020
as a 95 year old Holocaust
survivor from Auschwitz.

00:51:53.020 --> 00:51:57.450
And so I took that
down from the site.

00:51:57.450 --> 00:52:01.690 position:56%
And I just posted saying that anyone
who denies the Holocaust happens

00:52:01.690 --> 00:52:03.990
or denies that Joe
is anything but alive

00:52:03.990 --> 00:52:05.860
and well will not permitted
on this site.

00:52:05.860 --> 00:52:11.540
Because to do otherwise would be a
disservice and would be very awful

00:52:11.540 --> 00:52:15.540
for the memory of all those who
lost their lives including Joe's

00:52:15.540 --> 00:52:16.840
whole family.

00:52:16.840 --> 00:52:18.140
So I just won't allow that.

00:52:18.140 --> 00:52:19.610
But it was kind of
funny because right

00:52:19.610 --> 00:52:21.980
after that we were
at a party with Joe.

00:52:21.980 --> 00:52:24.270
It was a going away party for
my parents who actually lived

00:52:24.270 --> 00:52:25.750
in the same neighborhood.

00:52:25.750 --> 00:52:28.920
And so we were able to record
some fun video of saying, now,

00:52:28.920 --> 00:52:30.400
does Joe look dead to you?

00:52:30.400 --> 00:52:36.990
And he kept saying, no, I'm
alive and I'm well, and he is.

00:52:36.990 --> 00:52:43.870
&gt;&gt; Anthony Pitch: I tell you
when this book came out I wrote

00:52:43.870 --> 00:52:47.260
to the Southern Poverty Law Center

00:52:47.260 --> 00:52:50.190
and also the Simon
Wiesenthal Center.

00:52:50.190 --> 00:52:53.670
And I said I want to address Nazis.

00:52:53.670 --> 00:52:57.880
And I really was serious about it.

00:52:57.880 --> 00:52:59.970
And they both said to me don't.

00:52:59.970 --> 00:53:03.670 position:56%
First of all you won't get an
invitation, and if you do they'll be

00:53:03.670 --> 00:53:05.040
after you and your family.

00:53:05.040 --> 00:53:08.140
Now, I didn't mind if
they came for me because,

00:53:08.140 --> 00:53:11.580
as I said, I had a good life.

00:53:11.580 --> 00:53:14.880
But my family I wasn't
prepared for that.

00:53:14.880 --> 00:53:16.700
So I dropped that.

00:53:16.700 --> 00:53:19.120
But I want to leave
you with one subject.

00:53:19.120 --> 00:53:23.800
This is not about horror,
it's about heritage.

00:53:23.800 --> 00:53:29.000
And the people who deny the
Holocaust happened they probably

00:53:29.000 --> 00:53:31.080
haven't opened a book before.

00:53:31.080 --> 00:53:33.790
They don't only live in
the hills of Appalachia

00:53:33.790 --> 00:53:36.040
but they're all over the place.

00:53:36.040 --> 00:53:40.940
And this really is a
reputation of these people.

00:53:40.940 --> 00:53:48.120
The Jews have always survived
bequeathing a triumphant heritage

00:53:48.120 --> 00:53:49.420
of endurance.

00:53:49.420 --> 00:53:53.870
And the stories in my book testify
to this everlasting resilience.

00:53:53.870 --> 00:53:57.850
I phoned a fellow in Switzerland
just before his death last year,

00:53:57.850 --> 00:54:02.100
and he said to me,
he was a survivor,

00:54:02.100 --> 00:54:08.480
if the Holocaust never
happened where is my family?

00:54:08.480 --> 00:54:12.180
And so the deniers are the people

00:54:12.180 --> 00:54:14.800
who really are the
scum of the earth.

00:54:14.800 --> 00:54:16.810
They were not there.

00:54:16.810 --> 00:54:18.550
They haven't researched it.

00:54:18.550 --> 00:54:20.500
They haven't talked
to the survivors.

00:54:20.500 --> 00:54:23.920
How can they possibly know
what these people endured?

00:54:23.920 --> 00:54:27.720
&gt;&gt; Nancy Geise: And I was going
to say one more point to that.

00:54:27.720 --> 00:54:30.890
There are people right now
that deny 9/11 ever happened.

00:54:30.890 --> 00:54:33.440
A hundred years from now can
you imagine there will be a lot

00:54:33.440 --> 00:54:35.090
of people denying that
ever happened.

00:54:35.090 --> 00:54:38.210
People like to deny
that evil exists.

00:54:38.210 --> 00:54:41.360
Evil does exist.

00:54:41.360 --> 00:54:43.660
&gt;&gt; Michlean Amir: Unfortunately.

00:54:44.770 --> 00:54:46.080
One more question.

00:54:46.080 --> 00:54:47.380
Anyone have another question?

00:54:47.380 --> 00:54:50.520
All right, well, the authors
will remain around here

00:54:50.520 --> 00:54:52.020
if you'd like to speak with them.

00:54:52.020 --> 00:54:55.570
And, again, thank you
very much for coming.

00:54:55.570 --> 00:54:59.170
Gail, this was a very
successful program.

00:54:59.170 --> 00:55:03.720
Thank you very much for having us.

